        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-28 21:42:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThere is some degree of uncertainty on how long the http servers brought up in the junits will take (as they are brought up and down dynamically).   At least I don't know just yet, if I can extract the info using jetty apis.  \n\nIn any case, I have review \n\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/8799/\n\nwhere I introduced retries when getting \"ConnectExceptions\", so will retry several times before failing the test to accommodate for the variability and long delays for the servers to come up.\n\nI assume that the delays depend on the jenkins server load, and would assume was pretty busy this morning.",
        "patchset_number": 4
